## Bug Fixes

These mods fix bugs present in Vanilla Minecraft, other mods, or in loaders.

| Name                                                                                                | Description                                                                                                                                | Additional Notes                                                                                                                                                                                                                                           | Alternatives                                                     |
| --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | ---------------------------------------------------------------- |
| [AttributeFix](https://www.curseforge.com/minecraft/mc-mods/attributefix)                           | Removes arbitrary limits on Minecraft's attribute system                                                                                   | This mod is **not** able to modify the base attributes of players/mobs, only change the caps. For that functionality, check out our guide [here](https://modpack-dev-knowledgebase.github.io/modpack-dev-wiki/guide/items-blocks/attribute-modification/). | -                                                                |
| [Load My Fucking Tags](https://www.curseforge.com/minecraft/mc-mods/lmft)                           | Prevents Incorrect Tag Entries from breaking an entire Tag                                                                                 | -                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          | -                                                                |
| [Max Health Fix](https://www.curseforge.com/minecraft/mc-mods/max-health-fix)                       | Fixes a bug with max health in Minecraft                                                                                                   | -                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          | -                                                                |
| [Modernfix](https://www.curseforge.com/minecraft/mc-mods/modernfix)*                                | All-in-one mod that improves performance, reduces memory usage, and fixes many bugs                                                        | -                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          | -                                                                |
| [Too Fast](https://www.curseforge.com/minecraft/mc-mods/too-fast)                                   | Removes the server-side limitations on player speed that result in "player XYZ moved too fast" messages in the console and rubber-banding. | -                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          | [I'm Fast](https://www.curseforge.com/minecraft/mc-mods/im-fast) |
| [FTB Quests Kill Task Tweaks](https://www.curseforge.com/minecraft/mc-mods/quests-kill-task-tweaks) | Improves kill contribution tracking for FTB Quests                                                                                         | -                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          | -                                                                |
| [Simple Snowy Fix](https://www.curseforge.com/minecraft/mc-mods/simple-snowy-fix-forge-fabric)      | Fixes incorrect snow generation on tree leaves MC-119599                                                                                   | -                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          | -                                                                |
| [FTB Quests Freeze Fix](https://www.curseforge.com/minecraft/mc-mods/ftb-quests-freeze-fix)         | Caches the FTB Quests menu on startup to prevent freezing in game                                                                          | -                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          | -                                                                |

## Profiling/Debugging

These mods help profile and diagnose issues for modpacks, so that issues can be found and fixed.

| Name                                                                             | Description                                                                               | Additional Notes                                                                           | Alternatives |
| -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ | ------------ |
| [Crash Assistant](https://www.curseforge.com/minecraft/mc-mods/crash-assistant)* | Shows a GUI after Minecraft crashes, immediately showing and analyzing all affected logs. | -                                                                                          | -            |
| [Cyanide](https://www.curseforge.com/minecraft/mc-mods/cyanide)                  | Reduces data pack world generation pain by providing useful, informative error messages.  | -                                                                                          | -            |
| [Log Begone](https://www.curseforge.com/minecraft/mc-mods/log-begone)            | Allows you to stop entries from being logged in game console through phrases or regex     | -                                                                                          | -            |
| [Modernfix](https://www.curseforge.com/minecraft/mc-mods/modernfix)*             | All-in-one mod that improves performance, reduces memory usage, and fixes many bugs       | The `/modernfix mcfunctions` command can be used to diagnose unperformant datapacks/mods.  | -            |
| [Spark](https://www.curseforge.com/minecraft/mc-mods/spark)*                     | Performance profiler for Minecraft clients, servers and proxies                           | -                                                                                          | -            |
| [Observable](https://www.curseforge.com/minecraft/mc-mods/observable)            | Profiles (tile) entities and shows you what's taking up tick time and where               | -                                                                                          | -            |

\* - A must-have mod for nearly any modpack. Only in very rare circumstances should you not use this mod or an equivalent.

\** - Prone to issues or conflicts with other mods